@node "GBFOUTM" "Errors...."
Errors
------
When you start Yahtzee and the screen get's a colour (instead of black)
an errors has occured. Namely :
@{b}Red@{ub}.........The computer can not load file Yahtzee.NL or
            Yahtzee.GB. Yahtzee will not work. An error message will
            be displayed and you'll be forced to quit.
@{b}Purple@{ub}......The computer can not load file Yahtzee.SFX.
            Yahtzee wil work, but without sound effects.
@{b}Yellow@{ub}......The computer can not load file Yahtzee.MOD.
            Yahtzee wil work, but without music.
@{b}Light Blue@{ub}..The computer can not load file Yahtzee.SCR.
            Yahtzee will use the default background.
@{b}Green@{ub}.......The computer can not load file Yahtzee.IN.
            Yahtzee will use the default settings.
@{b}Blue@{ub}........The computer can not load file Yahtzee.HI.
            Yahtzee will use an empty Hi-Score.

When the computer wants to save the Hi-Score to disk and the screen
becomes @{b}blue@{ub} the computer could not save the Hi-Score.
When the computer wants to save the Settings to disk and the screen
becomes @{b}green@{ub} the computer could not save the Settings.
Check your disk if it's write protected or damaged.

It is possible that there is still a bug in Yahtzee.
If this happends you will see a red flashing square in the top of the
screen giving you an error number and some text.
Here's a list of some known error numbers.

09....Program interrupted
11....Var. space is gone
12....Can't open Math.Lib
13....Out of stack space
20....Devision by 0
23....Value of action wrong
24....Out of memory
29....Overflow
33....There is no data
47....Screen is not open
047 t/m 078....Screen/Window error
080 t/m 103....Disk error
108 t/m 117....Animation error

After an error you have to restart Yahtzee.

