@node "GBBACK" "Change background/music"
Change the background picture
=============================
All you have to do is to load YAHTZEE.SCR into your favourite paint
program, change it and save it instead of the YAHTZEE.SCR that was
allready there. You'll find YAHTZEE.SCR in the same directory as this
guide. Note: You HAVE to use the colours of the original picture.
Picture format: 320x256x32c (even in NTSC mode).

Change the music
================
You can replace Yahtzee.mod by any compatible protracker module.
Remember to save the new module as Yahtzee.mod.

@{"Go back to explanation" link "GBYAHTZ" b}
@endnode

@node "GBEND" "Final scores"
Final scores
------------
After each player has played for 13 rounds it's time to see the final
scores. Click on the YELLOW bar in the playfield. The computer will now
display the final scores. Click on 'OK' the continue to the main menu.
Click on STATISTICS (right from the OK) to view the statistics.
Leave statistics by clicking the 'OK' button. If a player got a HI-score
than this player's number will be highlighted. If a player got an alltime
HI than the whole column will be highlighted.

NTSC Amiga's: Click anywhere in the screen to continue or, to view the
Statistics, use the keyboard [A]. Press [O] to return to the final scores.

